# .chezmoiremove — target paths (in $HOME) that chezmoi should DELETE on apply.
# Use this to retire a dotfile across all machines: add its target path here,
# and on the next `chezmoi apply` it's removed everywhere (then you can drop the
# line). Supports templates. One target path per line, e.g.:
#   .config/zsh/rc.d/99-old-topic.zsh
#   .config/some-retired-tool
